arrival from Poland at Ellis Island in New York City in 1898.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">&nbsp;Excerpt from Cousin Magda&#39;s recipe book:</span></p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-tableplain ju-tight\" style=\"color: black; font-family: times new roman,serif; font-size: 14px; width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Where it all began. . .</strong><br /><br />In January of 1898, Stefan and Anna Kuchar arrived at Ellis Island. They jostled with the crowd that had made its way to the upper deck.&nbsp; Stefan carried all their worldly possessions in two small cases, while Anna carried only a small box with a leather strap.&nbsp; She clutched it to herself with one hand, holding Stefan&#39;s arm with the other.&nbsp; What did this carefully protected box contain?&nbsp; It was full of Anna&#39;s cookies!&nbsp; These cookies,&nbsp;hard when dry and chewy when moistened, had sustained the young couple on their long journey.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","headerText":""},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"7"},"leftText":"<p>At the reunion, family members congratulate you on the interesting details you provided about your great-grandparents in your speech.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br />You realize that you need to give credit to your Cousin Magda in your writing so that family members understand that she was the one who provided the interesting details.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">From your family history:</span></p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-tableplain\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td><span class=\"ju-double-space\" style=\"color:#552656;font-family:lato,sans-serif;font-size:15px;line-height:180%;\">Stefan and Anna Kuchar arrived at Ellis Island in the&nbsp;winter of 1898 <span class=\"marker\">(Kuchar, 2000)</span>.&nbsp; The story of Anna carrying only a single item off the ship--a small box of cookies--has been passed down through the generations. Those cookies were uniquely suited to travel because they were &quot;hard when dry and chewy when moistened&quot; <span class=\"marker\">(Kuchar, 2000, p. 25)</span>. The simple cookie provided the young couple with food as well as memories of home during the long voyage. The recipe still lives on in Anna&#39;s Famous Poppy Seed Cookies, available at Magda&#39;s Pastries.</span></td></tr></tbody></table>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":0,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":1,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"8"},"leftText":"<p><strong>2.&nbsp; Walsh, personal communication, December 25, 1972).&nbsp; <span class=\"marker\">Historian Richard Cox (1979)</span> tells us, &quot;After the 1920s, when trolleys and trains linked Coney Island to the rest of the city, a vast cross-section of New Yorkers gained access to its beaches, its rides, and its hoopla.&nbsp; By 1920, Coney Island had become a weekly destination for millions of city dwellers&quot;<span class=\"marker\"> (p.137)</span>.</span></td></tr></tbody></table>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":0,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":1,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"12"},"leftText":"<p><strong>4.&nbsp; You show off the research and hard work you have done.</strong></p>","rightText":null},{"settings":{"showAudio":0,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0},"leftText":"<p>You used many different resources to prepare your speech and essay.&nbsp; Comments from your family members suggest that they think this process was easy, but you know it wasn&#39;t.<br /><br />When they see your list of references, they will realize how much effort went into your writing.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>&nbsp;<span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">From your family history:</span></p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-tableplain\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td><p align=\"center\">References</p><p style=\"padding-left:20px;text-indent:-20px;line-height:2;\">Andrews, J.
